text: Île Marc is one of the Canadian arctic islands in Nunavut, Canada. It lies in the Boyer Strait, south of Massey Island, and north-west of Alexander Island. ==External links== * Île Marc in the Atlas of Canada - Toporama; Natural Resources Canada Ile Vanier Category:Uninhabited islands of Qikiqtaaluk Region Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago
title: Île Marc
